	situation of the main macroeconomic indicators and the imbalance in the relative prices of the economy. These measures included: (i) the issuance of Decree No. 55/2016, which declared an national statistic emergency and granted INDEC the necessary tools to restore international credibility regarding the indexes that it publishes; (ii) the relaxing of the foreign exchange system, (iii) the pre-agreement signed between the Argentina and the holdouts; (iv) the elimination or reduction of taxes on exports in order to improve the situation of regional economies; and (v) the process of adjustment of public services rates, including those collected by the Natural Gas Transportation business segment.


	At the date of issuance of this annual report there is uncertainty regarding the impact that these and other measures that the Government can take will have on key macroeconomic variables.



